description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for band 6 in Renal HDU at the Royal London Hospital in the specialist medicine division of renal and diabetes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bart’s Health is home to one of the UK’s largest renal &amp; haemodialysis unit, offering nurses the unique opportunity to work across a wide variety of clinical specialties and to advance their professional development. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our world class services include Medical, Surgical, Critical Care, Transplantation, Community Dialysis, Acute Dialysis, Research, Palliative Care, Renal Assessment, Living Donation, Acute Kidney Injury and Chronic Kidney Disease, based at our brand new hospital building near the City of London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Renal HDU team is a small and dynamic team based on the 9th floor with close working relationship with the transplant team as seen on Channel 5’s Operation Live.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have the HDU &amp; mentorship course&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be flexible and reliable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Raj Samraj, Unit Manager on 02035942653&lt;/p&gt;
